Help [=[

stat.dpois(s, l)
stat.ppois(s, l)
stat.qpois(p, l)
-------------------

Computes the probability mass function (`dpois`), cumulative distribution
function (`ppois`), and inverse cdf (`qpois`) for the *Poisson* distribution
with mean `l >= 0`. The density is given by `l^s * exp(-l) / s!` for
`s = 0, 1, ...`.
]=]
